Suez Environnement (SEV) , the second-largest water company in Europe, said it won contracts in  Hong
Kong  that include transferring dewatered sludge by boat for
treatment and the renewal of a waste collection agreement in
Macau valued at 310 million euros ($407 million).  The Paris-based utility said today in a statement that its
Sita subsidiary as part of a 10-year contract for the North
Lantau Transfer Station will be managing waste for the largest
of Hong Kongâ€™s islands, including Hong Kong International
